The paper deals with decoding of low-density parity-check codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves optimization problems and algorithms, which are relevant to computer science (cs.CC). The use of simulation and instanton analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of statistical learning (cs.SI). The paper also involves the use of linear programming and reweighted linear programming, which are topics in optimization and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves the comparison of different decoding algorithms, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
